text: A duplicate grass block texture appears in terrain.png to the right, for an unknown reason.
Added pre-release texture of water to terrain.png.
Added duplicates of the grass block side, top and bottom texture to terrain.png.
Added an unused texture to terrain.png.
Removed the grass block side, top and bottom texture duplicates and mysterious whitish texture from terrain.png.
The opaque water texture in terrain.png has been replaced with the dandelion texture.
Added a cobweb texture to terrain.png, but no associated block.
Added some unused variations of brick blocks to terrain.png.
Directly below these brick variations existed what appears to be a translucent bottom half of the block of gold side texture.
Slightly downwards and to the left existed a somewhat modified block of gold side texture, spread across four spaces.
Removed the brick variations and weird gold blocks from terrain.png.
Replaced the duplicate grass top texture with a duplicate lava placeholder texture.[verify]
Added a duplicate texture for planks and the infamous chair textures to terrain.png.
The duplicate planks texture has been replaced by the ladder texture.
The chair side texture has been darkened.
Added an second unused texture to terrain.png.
The unused chair textures have been removed from terrain.png.
The unknown white texture has been replaced by the snowy grass block side texture.
For some reason, the cake's item texture also appears on terrain.png as well as items.png. It is unused here.
Added a texture for crying obsidian to terrain.png. It was never used at this time.
The cobweb texture has been updated, and cobwebs have actually been implemented.
The crying obsidian texture has been replaced by the grass block overlay.
A duplicate grass block top texture has been added to terrain.png, potentially used as a palette for designing the adjacent grass and fern textures.
Added four unused textures to terrain.png.
An unused white cobblestone texture has been added to terrain.png.
The white cobblestone has been replaced with the end stone texture.
Despite being unused, the unused grass block top texture has been updated, and now has a distinct texture from the actually used grass block.
Two sandstone variant textures were added to terrain.png, but not used. These were indeed intended for use as sandstone block variants.[1]
The two unused sandstone textures from before have been replaced and the replacements implemented.
The unused cake texture, grass top duplicate and four unused blocks introduced in Beta 1.8 has been effectively removed with the splitting of block textures.
The famous unused paeonia texture has been added to the assets/minecraft/textures/blocks/ directory.
Added debug.png and debug2.png to the assets/minecraft/textures/blocks/ directory.
A duplicate of the blue shulker box top texture called test.png now exists directly in assets/minecraft/.
Despite being unused, a new paeonia texture has been included in a Texture Update resource pack.
Three extra variant textures for vines were also included, their uses unknown.
Removed the unused paeonia texture from the assets/minecraft/textures/blocks/ directory.

An unused texture sheet containing each texture then associated with the lectern has been added to the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory. It was used on the pre-release image but when replaced with separate textures before release.
The lectern sheet from above was removed from the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
The texture for a wax block was added to the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
Removed the wax block texture from the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
Two duplicate stripped warped stem textures are present in assets/minecraft/textures/block/, entitled "warped_stripped_log_top.png" and "warped_stripped_log_side.png".
Removed the above duplicate warped stem textures from the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
The textures "calibrated_sculk_sensor_top.png" and "calibrated_sculk_sensor_side.png" have been added to the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
The texture "root_vines_head.png" has beed added to the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
Removed the calibrated sculk sensor textures from the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
Removed the root vines texture from the assets/minecraft/textures/block/ directory.
The old web, cake item and crying obsidian textures are present in terrain.png.
Due to the absence of nether portals, its placeholder texture is unused.
The crying obsidian texture has been replaced by the grass block overlay, which is also unused in this edition.
terrain.png was split, removing some unused textures - specifics unknown.
Added what appear to be prototype textures for the Allow and Deny blocks.
The textures for allow and deny have been updated, and the blocks that use them actually implemented.[verify]
Added two unused barrel textures. Their fate remains unknown.
Added leather-chain armor and quiver sprites to items.png.
Added a bow texture to items.png, despite there not being bows at the time.
There is now a large purple curve in items.png
The bow texture has changed, and bows have been implemented, effectively removing the unused bow texture.
The purple curve has been removed.
Leather-chain armor's sprites have been removed.
Three copies of cat and two copies of 13 have been added to items.png as placeholders for future discs.
A ruby item texture has been added.
One of the extra cat discs has been replaced with the wait disc texture.
The texture for crystallized honey was added to the assets/minecraft/textures/item/ directory.
Removed the crystallized honey texture from the assets/minecraft/textures/item/ directory.
Nine identical item placeholder textures have been added to items.png.
Ten more identical item placeholder textures have been added to items.png, and one removed due to being replaced by the melon slice.
Five of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the fire charge, blaze rod, ghast tear, gold nugget and nether wart textures.

Twelve more identical item placeholder textures have been added to items.png, and six removed due to being replaced by the spider eye, fermented spider eye, blaze powder, magma cream and the two potion textures.
Three of the placeholder textures have been replaced with the brewing stand, cauldron and eye of ender textures.
Two of the placeholder textures have been replaced with the splash potion and glistering melon textures.
One of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the spawn egg texture.
One of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the spawn egg overlay texture.
One of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the bottle o' enchanting texture.
One of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the written book texture.
One of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the ruby texture.
Added 22 more placeholder textures to items.png.
Four of the placeholder textures have been replaced with the flower pot, empty map, nether star and item frame textures.
Added 11 more placeholder textures to items.png.
Five of the placeholder textures have been replaced with the carrot on a stick, skeleton and wither skeleton skull, and player and zombie head textures.
One of the placeholder textures has been replaced with the leather leggings overlay texture.
Four of the placeholder textures have been replaced with the firework rocket, enchanted book, and both firework star textures.
Three of the placeholder textures have been replaced with the comparator, nether quartz and nether brick textures.
items.png has now been removed, also removing all item placeholder textures.
A unused solid white player-shaped texture called 2char now exists in the game.
Removed 2char.png, likely due to texture pack support implementation.
Added some ender dragon textures. These two, entitled "body" and "dragon", are assumed unused due to being later removed.
Removed the door, pigman, weird villager, "body", "dragon" and skis textures.
Two particles were added that visually resemble water droplets, or possibly water or blue analogues of the existing "flame" and "lava" particles.
Added an angry villager head particle texture, which was unused.
The three unused particle textures have been removed with the splitting of particles.png.
The unused water/fire particle textures exist in this version of the game's particles.png.
The two older splash textures also added in this version had a very high likelihood of being unused.
The angry villager head particle now exists in particles.png.
Added a "soul lava" particle texture to particles.png.
Added add.png, trash.png, sm_multi.png, sm_options.png, sm_play.png.
sm_multi.png, sm_options.png, sm_play.png have been removed.
Showed pistons. The texture had extra band around the face, and smaller edge buckles.
A prototype version of the brewing stand is revealed.
A prototype enchanting table is revealed, once again.
A prototype enchanting table is revealed. The top texture is now identical to a release.
Showcased an image featuring colored wood planks, which ultimately never made it into the game.
This texture was shown for wet sponges.
Jeb showcases updated wool colors. Some may not have made it into 17w06a, however this is currently unknown.
Prototypes for coral were shown in a clip at MINECON Earth.
This honey block was showcased at MINECON Live 2019.
This version of the spore blossom was shown at at Minecraft Live 2020.
Deepslate was shown unnamed as part of deep dark caves biome at Minecraft Live 2020.
The sculk sensor and these sculk blocks were shown off at Minecraft Live 2020.
These textures were used for the reveal of copper related blocks.
This sculk sensor texture was shown.
This sculk block texture was shown.
This sculk sensor texture was shown.
This sculk veins texture was shown.
This sculk veins texture was shown.
The sculk block has a new texture in a tweet from Brandon Pearce.
Henrik Kniberg shows this modified dandelion texture for testing purposes.
JAPPA tweets an image of an alternate tuff texture.
Showed new animated texture of active tendril.
32px The big dripleaf has a new texture in a tweet from Agnes Larsson.
The big dripleaf has a new texture in a tweet from Agnes Larsson.
JAPPA tweets an image of alternate hanging roots and rooted dirt textures.
Showed early design of glow lichen.
Henrik Kniberg shows grimstone variants of overworld ore.
JAPPA shows new textures of iron ore, gold ore and updated grimstone variants of overworld ore.
JAPPA shows a new texture for the grimstone variant of diamond ore.
JAPPA shows updated iron ore, copper ore, redstone ore and updated grimstone variant of overworld ore.
JAPPA shows the new texture of deepslate.
xilefian shows one of 18 different concepts of pointed dripstone created in October 2020, and early textures of dripstone block.
A rejected observer texture is released.
Jeb tweets the first image containing updated textures. Included are unreleased obsidian and birch log textures. The grass texture also changed, but whether this was released is unknown.
Jeb showed new textures of obsidian and block of diamond.
Jeb replies with an image of all the new logs.
JAPPA tweets an image of a less-blurry birch log.
Jeb tweets an image of an unreleased jungle planks texture.
JAPPA showed second new texture of block of diamond.
Showed new texture of block of emerald.
JAPPA tweets an image of new crafting table, oak planks, and oak wood.
Showed new textures of chorus flower and chorus plant.
Showed new textures of stone bricks, mossy stone bricks, cracked stone bricks, chiseled stone bricks and vines.
Compared new textures from previous post with old one.
Showed new second textures of oak planks and oak log.
Showed new textures of hay bale.
Showed new textures of dead bush and cactus.
Showed new textures of glass and wheat.
Showed new second texture of cobblestone.
Showed new textures of skeleton and mossy cobblestone (and torch?).
Compared textures of oak planks from previous post and old one.
Showed new second texture of glowstone.
Showed new texture of cave spider.
Showed new texture of block of quartz, quartz pillar block and chiseled quartz block.
Showed closer new texture of chiseled quartz block from previous post.
Showed closer new texture of sand (and husk?).
Showed new textures of zombie and carved pumpkin.
Showed new texture of pigman, netherrack, soul sand, nether bricks and spawner.
Showed new texture of red mushroom.
Showed closer new texture of soul sand from previous posts.
Showed maybe new textures of grass block, oak leaves, [[]], pumpkin pie, wheat, cauldron, redstone dust, slimeball, apple, saddle, iron ingot, feather and new third texture of oak log.
Same textures from previous post, but all items dropped from inventory.
Showed new textures of wolf, stone, andesite and coal ore. Updated textures of apple and feather.
Showed new textures of cake in block and item forms, jungle boat, carrot in item form, water bottle, totem of undying, minecart with furnace in item form, cookie, bucket, emerald and more.
Showed closer textures of cake in block form.
Showed closer texture of totem of undying.
Showed new textures of block of gold, block of emerald and third new texture of block of diamond.
Showed closer textures from previous post.
Showed closer texture of spawner and cobblestone from previous post (or new).
Showed new textures of pig, spider, chicken, melon, gravel, birch leaves, rose bush and dandelion.
Showed new textures of sheep and snow.
Showed new texture of snow golem.
Showed new textures of redstone ore, diamond ore, gold ore, emerald ore and red sand.
Showed new second texture of glass.
Showed new second textures of brich leaves and brich logs.
Showed new third texture of oak planks.
Showed new textures of redstone lamp and acacia leaves.
Showed new second texture of jungle boat in item form.
Showed new texture of diamond and new second texture of diamond ore.
Showed new second textures of block of gold, block of emerald and fourth texture of block of diamond.
Showed new second texture of jungle boat in item form.
Showed new third texture of block of emerald.
JAPPA tweets an image of updated obsidian.
JAPPA tweets an image of updated diorite and andesite.
Showed new textures of oak log, stone, cobblestone and glass "This is just soms tests, exploring. Not V3."
Showed new textures of oak log, stone, cobblestone and glass. "Sometimes, to explore options and things I try drastic changes like this:"
Showed new second textures of stone and granite.
Showed new textures of obsidian and golden sword.
Showed new textures of spruce log, spruce planks.
Showed new textures of ice, packed ice and new second texture of snow.
Compared textures from previous post and old one.
Showed new textures of sand and cactus.
Showed new textures of sandstone, cut sandstone, chiseled sandstone and cactus.
Showed new textures of oak log and oak planks.
Jasper Boerstra tweets an image from the boat texturing process. A new (probably experimental) cobblestone and mossy cobblestone can be seen atop the background.
Showed new texture of skeleton horse.
Showed new textures of zombie horse and skeleton horse.
Showed new textures of stained glass.
Showed new texture of block of quartz.
A teaser image for cooked chicken is revealed by Jeb.

texts.text: This page intends to document the history of textures used in Minecraft.
For more in depth information for actually used textures for each edition, refer to the following pages:

Java Edition history of textures
Bedrock Edition history of textures
Education Edition history of textures
Legacy Console Edition history of textures
New Nintendo 3DS Edition history of textures
Pi Edition history of textures

1 Unused textures
1.1 Blocks
1.2 Items
1.3 Entities
1.4 Particles
1.5 Miscellaneous
2 Developer version exclusive textures
2.1 Blocks
2.2 Items
3 References
For more information on these, see History of textures/Unused textures.

These textures appeared exclusively in development screenshots or videos. In most cases, the raw files have never been released publicly; all cases documented here are derived from recreations unless otherwise stated.
" Decided to redo the "heiroglyph" sandstone blocks and enable them in the game. Will be in 1.2.4, both creative and survival" – @jeb_ on Twitter, March 30, 2012
